Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut crosswise into
1/2-inch-thick half-moons. Peel, halve, and finely dice @onion{1}(peeled and
finely diced). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Pick fronds
from @dill{1/4%ounce} and finely chop half; reserve remaining for serving.
Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

In a small #pot{}, bring @Israeli couscous{5%ounce} and @water{1 1/2%cups} to a
boil. Once boiling, cover and reduce heat to low; cook until al dente,
~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
zucchini and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and softened,
~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add onion,
garlic, and @shrimp{10%ounce}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is
softened and shrimp is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @cream
cheese{2%tablespoon}, chopped dill, @water{1/2%cup}, and juice from half the
lemon. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}
more.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Add couscous and zucchini to pan with shrimp mixture. Cook, stirring, until
combined, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted and combined. Taste and
season with salt and pepper.

Divide couscous between #plates{} or #bowls{}. Sprinkle with lemon zest and
remaining dill. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.